The article discusses the issue of budget and spending in Washington, highlighting the national debt of over $21 trillion and the potential $1 trillion deficit for next year. President Trump has proposed spending cuts to address this issue, seeking to eliminate outdated and ineffective programs. The Office of Management and Budget has been working to identify wasteful spending already approved by Congress. President Trump will send a $15.4 billion rescissions request to Congress, which would be the largest ever using this authority. The article emphasizes the need for responsible spending and fiscal restraint in order to avoid burdening future generations with debt.